<br>
Personally, I <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>love</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Malosini</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> line of spells, and helping my brother <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Wizards</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> and myself do more damage.<br>
<br>
Comments appreciated.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Razamatazz Pizzazz<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> <br>
Senior ArchMage, Ancient Fellowshi</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ujarnin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jarnin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br>  Posts: 1533<br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/18/02 6:23 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Area Effect Malosini?</span><hr size=1> The problem with an AoE debuff like that is:<br>
<br>
1. They're usually have a massive taunt.<br>
2. They usually don't work as well as the single target versions.<br>
3. Resists will make them not as useful.<br>
<br>
If you want to know how useful this would be, head to a chanter board and ask them how often they use the spell <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Winds of Tashani</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->. Most will tell you it's a insta-aggro death spell. <p><center>
